	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs5E1DB61D">WEST virginia legislature</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 regular session</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">ENGROSSED</span></p><p class="csC8B78D2C"><span class="csC2FEE544">Committee Substitute</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">for</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4053</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Hall, Fehrenbacher, Crouse, Drennan, Heckert, Holstein, Moore, Pinson, Shamblin, and Hillenbrand</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Originating in the Committee on the Judiciary;<br/>Reported on February 4, 2026]</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by creating a new article and accompanying sections, designated 15-3G1, &sect;15-3G-2, &sect;15-3G-3, &sect;15-3G4, &sect;15-3G-5, and &sect;15-3G-6, related to findings and establishing start date of the Blue Envelope Program; relating to establishing the &quot;blue envelope&quot; program; relating to establishing standards for storage, retention of &nbsp;information relating to a person&rsquo;s identity; relating to the prohibiting any person or entity from having the State Police verify any information contained on the envelope; and providing that No person or entity who in good faith follows and abides by the provisions of this article is liable for any civil or criminal penalty as the result of any act or omission in the furtherance thereof unless it is alleged and proven that the information disclosed was false and disclosed with the knowledge that the information was false.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="csDCDA41A9"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="csEA1688">
		<span class="cs785A50A6">CHAPTER 15</span></h2>
	<h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 3g. BLUE ENVELOPE PROGRAM. </span></h2>
	<p class="csDCDA41A9"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;15-3G-1. &nbsp;Short title.</span></h4>
	<h4 class="cs53FB8D75">
		<span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall be known and may be cited as &quot;Blue Envelope Program&quot;.</span></h4>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;15-3G-2. &nbsp;Findings relating to the &ldquo;Blue Envelope Program&rdquo;.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) By January 1, 2027, the West Virginia State Police, in consultation with relevant stakeholders, shall develop a &ldquo;Blue Envelope Program&rdquo; to promote inclusivity and enhanced communication between law enforcement and community members with a condition or disability where additional accommodations or awareness may be helpful. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The West Virginia State Police shall develop and implement a program for the promotion, printing, and distribution of envelopes for use by drivers diagnosed with autism spectrum disorder, dementia, or intellectual and developmental disabilities to provide to a law enforcement officer for the purpose of easing communication during a traffic stop or upon such law enforcement officer&rsquo;s arrival at the scene of a traffic accident.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<a name="_Hlk221033957"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;15-3G-3. &nbsp;Establishment of the &ldquo;Blue Envelope Program&rdquo;.</span></a></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) &nbsp;The &ldquo;Blue Envelope Program&rdquo; shall provide durable, blue-colored envelopes to persons with autism spectrum disorder, dementia, or intellectual and developmental disabilities.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The West Virginia State Police shall make &ldquo;Blue Envelope Program&rdquo; materials available by mail and at every West Virginia State Police detachment and county motor vehicle office.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Such blue envelopes shall:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Clearly state that the driver has been diagnosed with an autism spectrum disorder, dementia, or intellectual and developmental disabilities with an autism spectrum disorder and have printed directions for law enforcement officers on best practices for interacting with such driver with traffic stop safety tips;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Provide space for more information to be written about the driver&rsquo;s communication needs and recommendations to the responding law enforcement officer with interaction techniques to help promote enhanced communication and accommodation between law enforcement and community members to effectively communicate, reduce stress and ensure everyone&rsquo;s safety during interactions with law enforcement;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Have a blank area where the driver, or their emergency contact, may add additional noteworthy comments pertaining to the driver&rsquo;s individual needs or requested accommodations and where the driver may write down the contact information of their emergency contact person;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Be of sufficient size to fit into the glove compartment of a motor vehicle and be able to hold a driver&rsquo;s license, vehicle registration card, vehicle insurance card and other related documents; and,</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) Have printed directions instructing the driver to place his or her proof of vehicle registration and insurance in the envelope and provide such envelope and his or her driver&rsquo;s license to law enforcement if he or she is ever involved in a traffic stop or traffic accident. &nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<a name="_Hlk221034017"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;15-3G-4. &nbsp;Collection and storage of information.</span></a></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The West Virginia State Police shall not collect or store information identifying any person who has requested or received such an envelope, except any information necessary to distribute such an envelope to the requestor. &nbsp;No such information shall be stored in any form after the distribution of such envelope is complete.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<a name="_Hlk221034109"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;15-3G-5. &nbsp;Verification of information by State Police.</span></a></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">Nothing herein shall require the West Virginia State Police to verify any information provided on the envelope. &nbsp;No action taken by any person, whether private citizen or public officer or employee, with regard to any information provided on the envelope shall create a warranty of the reliability or accuracy of the document, nor shall it create any liability on the part of the State of West Virginia or any department, office, or agency or of any officer, employee or agent thereof.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;15-3G-6. &nbsp;Immunity from civil or criminal liability.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">No person or entity who in good faith follows and abides by the provisions of this article is liable for any civil or criminal penalty as the result of any act or omission in the furtherance thereof unless it is alleged and proven that the information disclosed was false and disclosed with the knowledge that the information was false.</span></p>


